The Dog Spotter Backend Challenge

Requirements:
Stack - CakePHP, VueJs, MySQL. No UI frameworks or style libraries. CSS/SCSS only. Deploy on AWS. You can create a free account here - https://aws.amazon.com/free/?all-free-tier.sort-by=item.additionalFields.SortRank&all-free-tier.sort-order=asc

Task - Where have you seen different dog breeds?

Build a simple single page app that:
	- allows users to input the dog names, dog breeds, locations, and time they saw these dogs and then save this information in the database.
	- represents all of the locations where these dog have been seen with Google Maps - you should use the relevant Google Maps API information - https://developers.google.com/maps/documentation
	- each dog breed should be represented by a image of that dog breed on the map

To submit this task, please provide a github repository with the solution and a link to access the deployed solution.
